1998.assessment:
Kabila breaks with Rwanda/Uganda — triggers Second Congo War. AFDL dissolved.
Elite completely fragmented: Kabila backed by Angola/Zimbabwe/Namibia;
Rwanda/Uganda backing RCD; MLC; numerous other factions. Complete fragmentation.

2003.assessment:
1+4 formula: Kabila + 4 VPs (Jean-Pierre Bemba/MLC; Azarias Ruberwa/RCD-Goma;
Arthur Z'ahidi Ngoma; Yerodia Ndombasi). Formal power-sharing. Elite competition
managed within transitional framework but significant tensions. Significant competition managed.
